<content5 releasenbr="1">
<step1>
<ptxt>DATA LIST</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Using the intelligent tester's DATA LIST allows switch, sensor, actuator, and other item values to be read without removing any parts. Reading the DATA LIST early in troubleshooting is one way to save time.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<step2>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG).</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the tester on.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / AIR CONDITIONER / DATA LIST.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
